summary: This document is a financial statement from Deutsche Bank detailing account transactions for the period from September 1, 2016, to September 30, 2016. It includes information on deposits, withdrawals, and fees associated with the account, highlighting the account balance and various transactions made during the month.
keyFacts: The account had a beginning balance of $107,561.86 on September 1, 2016.
The ending balance as of September 30, 2016, was $64,723.08.
Multiple preauthorized debits were made throughout September, including payments to ADP for payroll fees and Oxford Health premiums.
No overdraft fees were incurred during this statement period.
The document includes instructions for reporting errors related to electronic and non-electronic funds transfers.
